Lending platform, FairMoney MicroFinance Bank, has evolved into a digital bank. The credit-led digital bank said it is geared to revolutionise banking by extending new and improved banking features to all its customers. The bank with a track record of disbursing over N117 million loans as at December 2021, said some of the features of Fair Banking include account opening with zero balance, high-interest investment opportunities, 24/7 access to reliable digital banking services, 3% discount on airtime and data purchase, Free FairMoney Debit cards, 100 free bank transfers monthly, hitch less bill payments all on the FairMoney App. Head, marketing & branding, Nengi Akinola explained: “At FairMoney Microfinance Bank, one of our leading goals is to enable each and everyone of our users to achieve their dearest dreams, giving them a fair chance to rise against all odds. This is what Fair banking for all represents, catering for as many as would join the FairFam and leaving no one aside”. 